content: Invested time in personal development. Reading "Thinking, Fast and Slow" to understand cognitive biases in trading. Knowledge is power.
Struggling with a complex AI model. The code isn't cooperating. It's like trying to herd cats. But I'm learning more about debugging.
A breakthrough! Managed to optimize an algorithm for better market prediction. It's a small step, but every step counts.
Attended a trading seminar. Met some traders with different philosophies. Eye-opening to see how diverse trading strategies can be.
Feeling the pressure of being jobless. But, I'm using this time to reflect and strengthen my trading strategies. Every challenge has its purpose.
Had a heart-to-heart with family. Their support is my backbone, reminding me why I'm pushing through these tough times.
Just got an email. I'm in for a quant internship! The hard work and rejections paid off. It's a new beginning.
First day at the internship. The pace is intense, but I'm here to learn, grow, and make an impact. Here we go.
